	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>What should a wizard's weaknesses be?</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#330066" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>A fundamental rule of class based MMORPG's (or co-op multiplayer games in general) is interreliance.  Every class should have strengths that appeal to other players as well as weaknesses that require them to seek out other classes.  The reason for this is that it's an encouragement for a more social community, a Very Good Thing for any MMORPG.  This can be carried out through different fashions; a lack of ability to advance your character without the help of others (in EQ, the cleric/warrior combination is a good example of this), the strengthening of your character when placed with other classes (enchanters/shamans and dps classes), amongst other means.<br />
<br />
It's clear that wizards here want to be doing damage; and being a magic based damage dealer, it would make the most sense to me that wizards would be strongly placed in the &quot;gains power through grouping&quot; role.<br />
<br />
There's a lot of talk on these boards about what wizards should be able to do; but what weaknesses should a wizard have that encourage him (or her) to find a group?<br />
<br />
This isn't an invitation to list off what wizards can't do; for instance, I know wizards can't heal.  That's class definition; certain classes are designed for certain roles.  I'm curious as to what your opinions are on what checks the game should have to encourage wizards to group, beyond gamewide ones such as the grouping xp modifier and social reasons.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
