		<!-- message -->
		<div>Well as I agree that we must give something and get others things. And I think we give more than we get back atm. <br />
<br />
I assume, I dont know if all agree, but I still assume that we was all OK when the game was released. During which time we actually was DPS and was good at killing mobs. As you and everyone else knows we lost alot during Kunark and Velious, when Luclin and pop came we got back some of what was lost. We got better, but not as much as we was in the beginning(comparable to mobs hp/dps). So we was still behind, but we liked it, we was so much better off than in Velious.<br />
We also changed with luclin/pop well you might say it started in Velious but we changed, we could nolonger play like we did before, mobs had alot more hp now, but our spells was not as much bigger. And this trend continued in GoD and oow, mobs hp went up, mob dps went up. Our spells went up but not comparable.<br />
<br />
Our weaknesses is very very clear. Among others are:<br />
We have low hp (silk class)<br />
We have little ac (silk class)<br />
We are very limited to aggro (so limited to tank)<br />
We are limited by mana ( low mana regen, and high usage )<br />
We are weak when we dont have debuffers in group. (way too many resists, even cold spells in pofire are resisted once in a whlie)<br />
On raids we are weak if mobs are not fully debuffed.<br />
Resists take full mana and give full / double(?) aggro. <br />
<br />
There is probably more of these limitation we have as a wizard. We are supposed to be good at damage, ATM we are not even that. In xp groups with high uptime we are lower dps than a paladin... and if group doesnt have chanter and chanter buff fade... /shrug I am embarrased by being in group leeching xp when my DPS sucks.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				You start casting Ancient Core Fire<br />
You deliver a critical blast! (26)
			</div>
		<!-- / sig -->
		
		
		
	
	</td>
