			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>Wizards weakness?</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#330066" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Pushing aside the obvious banter, I think the main wizardly weaknesses should balance out as follows:<br />
<br />
Wizards should be poor at taking physical damage.  With lower AC, silk class damage mitigation, lack of defensive AA abilities and lower overall hitpoints, this seems to be in place.<br />
<br />
Wizards should be poor at dealing physical damage.  Beyond the lack of major melee based skills and AA already, I actually think we could afford to be nerfed more.  Reduce the enhancement provided by haste items and spells used on us.  Decrease our haste cap significantly, or make us ineligible targets for haste spells.  Give us an inherent penatly to weapon process or remove the ability for critical process.<br />
<br />
Wizards should be poorer at running away.  We're not a physically active bunch, and it should show in our speed.  I'm not sure how this would implement, but it seems appropriate to me that we should be able to rely more upon a shadowstep or portal ability (give us a step spell that sends us in our current facing direction only) and less upon the power of our legs.<br />
<br />
That's what I have on the top of my head.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
