	<div align="center">
		<div class="page" style="width:100%; text-align:left">
			<div style="padding:0px 25px 0px 25px">
<div style="padding:0px 0px 6px 0px">

<table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center">
<tr>
	<td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" >		
			<!-- status icon and date -->
			<a name="post614836"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/statusicon/post_old.gif" alt="Old" border="0" /></a>
			
				February 9th, 2005, 07:30 AM
			
			
			<!-- / status icon and date -->				
	</td>
	<td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" align="right">
		&nbsp;
		

		 #<a href="showpost.php?s=b32190d8d30ec2d2f4d57b612137959f&amp;p=614836&amp;postcount=13" target="new"><strong>13</strong></a>
	</td>
</tr>
<tr valign="top">
	<td class="alt2" width="175">
			
			<div id="postmenu_614836">
				<a class="bigusername" href="member.php?s=b32190d8d30ec2d2f4d57b612137959f&amp;u=112">Ravilicus</a>
				<script type="text/javascript"> vbmenu_register("postmenu_614836", true); </script>
			</div>
                        


			<div class="smallfont">My spoon's too big</div>
			
			
			<!-- Avatars -->		
			
			<!-- If WoW-style Avatars... -->
			
				<div class="smallfont">
					&nbsp;<br /><a href="member.php?s=b32190d8d30ec2d2f4d57b612137959f&amp;u=112"><img src="image.php?s=b32190d8d30ec2d2f4d57b612137959f&amp;u=112&amp;dateline=1075404990" alt="Ravilicus's Avatar" border="0" /></a>
				</div>
			
			
			<!-- /Avatars -->
			<div class="smallfont">
<br>



<br />
<div>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=393954" target="blank">Magelo Profile</a></div>

</div>
				
				<div>
					
					
				</div>
				<div>   </div>
			</div>					
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>All caster classes have the same weaknesses in differing degrees and with different tools to mitigate them:<br />
<br />
-(Low) Hp levels<br />
-Poor damage mitigation<br />
-Lack of skills for avoiding melee<br />
-Poor melee skills (not a weakness so much as lack of a particularly sustainable offensive ability)<br />
-Reliance on mana pool to be effective<br />
-Fizzles<br />
-Interruptions<br />
-Resists/Immunities<br />
-Aggro Management<br />
-Casting and Recast times, and the anchoring in place that is necessary to cast<br />
-Spell Reflection (minor concern by comparison to others listed above, very circumstancial currently)<br />
<br />
Any other weaknesses aren't specifically weaknesses per se, they are just having a lack of skills/abilities/spells that enable the class to perform a particular role, such as CC or puller.  Certain abilities like Pacify, Feign Dead, Escape, etc. make siingle pulling/splitting spawns much easier.  Slow and mezz make CC much easier, etc.<br />
<br />
Wizards are challenged to an equal or greater degree than all other caster classes with weaknesses listed in the above list with the exception of being arguablly better at avoiding melee damage than the Mage class due to our Forceshield line of spells.  Mages fair better in sustainable damage however due to their pets, mod rods, and damage shield spells.<br />
<br />
I like the Wizard class.  I like the spell selection we have and the role we play.  However, I feel that after level 60 many of the abilities we have enjoyed from lower levels become obsolete and ineffectual.  Particularly against level 70 high end content, our stun spells are worthless, mobs are either immune or highly resistant to Root, and our Shields spells are destroyed by a single hit as opposed to a full quad attack.  With mobs flurrying and rampaging and dishing out insane DPS our shields serve no purpose other than an AE damage (non DoT!) mitigation.<br />
<br />
Our spells no longer do as large a % of a target's HP total as they used to, and our sustainable damage is highly dependent on other classes and their buffs/recourses.  There used to be a good balance between our mana levels with adequete DPS and the mana levels of the healer classes participating in the same group.  This is no longer the case, especially since heals do not face the problem with resists than is the greatest limitation to Wizard DPS.  Yes, Wizard have Lure and &quot;bane&quot; spell lines, but the problem is that the class is forced to use those spells on the majority of content in order to produce reliable damage, and so their efficiency and sustainable DPS suffers even more.<br />
<br />
Lets look at the major &quot;roles&quot; that are desirable for a typical group of adventure-seekers:<br />
<br />
1) Meat Shield.  Gotta have a tank!  So is the decree of class balance and cooperative play.  To the dismay of the Knight classes, this may actually mean &quot;Gotta have a Warrior&quot; if your group isn't decked out in the best raid gear available and you are attempting to engage more challenging content.<br />
<br />
2) Healer.  Similar to Meat Shield, this may be synonymous with &quot;Cleric&quot;, depending on how concerned your group is with maximizing it's effectiveness.<br />
<br />
3) Slower/Debuffer.  These days, mobs aren't just tough.  As a matter of fact many of them are gimpy; however, they are <i>dangerous</i>, and need to have their damage output mitigated.  Slow is a must against challenging content at the high end.  Other debuffs also make it easier to defeat the target, as resistances are high.<br />
<br />
4) Puller.  The group needs to be able to engage targets without being overwhelmed.  CC and/or splitting are necessary.<br />
<br />
5) Support, or &quot;DPS&quot;.  Beyond the above, the rest of the group can be filled with just about <i>any</i> class.  Another &quot;off-tank&quot;, or a secondary healer, or a class with group friendly buffs or abilities, or one that boosts the group's DPS and helps kill mobs faster.<br />
<br />
#5 is the role filled by the majority of classes, including Wizards, because <i>any</i> class can fill this role.  Even clerics (who are the most defensively-oriented class in the game) can dish out adequete sustained DPS with melee, pets and nukes when the need arises (especially against Undead).<br />
<br />
This is where the <b>real</b> &quot;weakness&quot; of the Wizard class becomes apparent.  Resists, fizzles, and reliance on mana don't make us appear to suck nearly as much as the fact that we compete with every other class in the game for a position in a single group, and have no ability to adequetely fill one of the top 4 roles in even a supplemental fashion.<br />
<br />
We could be the most absurdly weak class in every manner whatsoever, but even if we had ONE ability that made us invaluable to groups (I.E. Slow, or Complete Heal, etc.) then we would be more reasonablly &quot;balanced&quot; and you wouldn't hear so many complaints.  I believe the same could be said if we could maintain our position amongst the best DPS classes (long and short term).</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
