	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Although casters in general are physically weaker than others, wizards should be  an extreme case of this.  Their weakness should be greater than others, but their strength should also be greater than others.   Wizards are NOT a well-rounded class in any game or any concepts.<br />
<br />
I picture the image of wizards as a class that has paid everything for a complete dominance in magical destruction.  They should be the weakest class upclose and 10 year old child could beat up an OOM wizard.  Wits and cunning with bit of magic should be the only thing that protects wizards from close range.  But from far range and FM, a pissed-off wizard should have no rival in terms of amount of damage unleashed.  Everyone, even allies, should tremble in fear and make a way for a wizard who is about to unleash deaths delivered by magic.<br />
<br />
My personal preference is that I can give up ports, solo ability, root, snare and whatnot for increase in damage.  I will be happy as long as wizards are in the top of damange dealers in a group/raid, 50% or more above than any other class.  Wizards should be able to single-shot kill an even-con mobs using their entire manapool (manaburn).  But that's just me <img src="images/smilies/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Big Grin" class="inlineimg" /></div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
