		<!-- message -->
		<div>Sure Sinari managed to divine your point but gave zero actual input.  Very typical.<br />
<br />
Claud set up an experiment and Graffe's as a whole failed.  Ohhh. I am so sad.<br />
<br />
Now back to the point.  If Claud had read Rav's post he would have noticed an actual comparison between wizards and other dps classes and strs/weakness of same.  Yes it wasn't as narrow as Claud wanted.  Sorry we didn't obey your thoughts claud.<br />
<br />
I think the issue is that on a macro level there is nothing wrong.  It is the details that are the problem.  Our existing weaknesses are fine.  We don't need to be any worse at soloing to try to get groups, we are all looking for groups now.    But...the details.<br />
<br />
* My burst dps isn't bursting high enough.  <br />
* My sustained dps is now below that of warriors, and beastlords.<br />
* Mana efficiency on my big nukes are now much closer percentage wise to mage efficiencies.  We need a wider gap again.<br />
* Size of our nukes are too close to other classes, wider gap needed.<br />
* Resists are outdated.  Because wizards have a &quot;Class&quot; idea of -10 to all resists that is what we get.  Other classes now are getting -50, -75, etc on their spells but ... we still get -10 on normal, -50 on sparks, -300 on banes.  This needs to be adjusted so we have options again without horrible mana ratio.<br />
<br />
All of these issues were less during luclin, pop.  The ratio of our benefits needs to get back to those days.  Our weaknesses have been consistantly increased.  Our strengths need to go back to previous levels.<br />
<br />
This is a detail level issue not a macro level issue as Claud wants to discuss.  Spell by spell needs to be examined and the ratios need to be adjusted.  Just that alone would make a huge difference.<br />
<br />
Then fix FD to make it a real burst AA not a zero sum game.</div>
